text: Anselmo Gonzaga was a Filipino sprinter. He competed in the 100 m and 200 m events at the 1928 Summer Olympics, but failed to reach the finals. Gonzaga won one gold and two silver medals in these events at the Far Eastern Championship Games, which were a precursor to the Asian Games.
